**Abstract:**
French-language abstract of article on Leibniz's early writings: "Métaphysique et Eucharistie dans les écrits de jeunesse de Leibniz." Argues Leibniz's early effort to link mechanical philosophy to theism led him to emphasize God as Prime Mover, but his desire to defend transubstantiation inspired development of metaphysical analyses of substantiality and divine union with world. Notes growing tension between his metaphysics and defense of transubstantiation during Paris period, related to principle of equipollence and increasing centrality of nature's intelligibility and autonomy.

